Get all recipes
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/
HTTP Method: GET
JSON response:
[
    {
        "id": 2,
        "user": 1,
        "name": "make Taco",
        "step": [
            {
                "id": 2,
                "recipe": 2,
                "step_text": "Take Tortilla"
            }
        ],
        "ingredient": [
            {
                "id": 1,
                "recipe": 2,
                "ingredient_text": "Cheese"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": 3,
        "user": 1,
        "name": "Make coffee",
        "step": [
            {
                "id": 4,
                "recipe": 3,
                "step_text": "Boil milk"
            },
            {
                "id": 5,
                "recipe": 3,
                "step_text": "Add coffee powder"
            }
        ],
        "ingredient": [
            {
                "id": 2,
                "recipe": 3,
                "ingredient_text": "Coffee"
            }
        ]
    }
]


******Add Recipe******
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/
HTTP Method: POST
Request Format:
{ 
	"name"    : "Make Tea",
	"user_id" : 1 
}

JSON Response:
If successful
{
    "id": 5,
    "user": 1,
    "name": "Make tea",
    "step": [],
    "ingredient": []
}


*****Update Recipe*****
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/recipe_id/
HTTP Method: PUT/PATCH 
Request Format
{ 
	"name"    : "Recipe_name" 
} 

JSON Response
{
    "id": 5,
    "user": 1,
    "name": "Recipe_name",
    "step": [],
    "ingredient": []
}


*****Delete Recipe*****
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/recipe_id
HTTP Method: DELETE 


*****Retrieve all recipes by particular user*****
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/user/user_id
HTTP Method: GET
Response: Gets all recipes by this user if user is in the database. Otherwise, it will throw an error


*****Add Steps*****
Endpoint: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/recipes/recipe_id/step/
HTTP method: POST

Request Response:
{
    "step_text": "step_name"
}

JSON Response:
{
    "id": 7,
    "recipe": recipe_id,
    "step_text": "step_name"
}

*****Add Ingredients*****
{
    "ingredient_text": "Ingredient"
}

JSON Response:
{
    "id": 7,
    "recipe": recipe_id,
    "ingredient_text": "Ingredient"
}


For more information about the how to send responses and retrieve responses, check out api/urls.py
